{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/bigint\/aboutbfraction"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Signed fractions with numerator and denominator of unbounded size"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Articles","identifiers":["doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutBInt","doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutCRT","doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Algorithms","doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Performance","doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/References"],"title":"Articles"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fractions are represented as "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/BFraction","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" values consisting of a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/BInt","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" numerator value and a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/BInt","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" denominator value. The representation is normalized:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The numerator and denominator have no common factors except 1"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The denominator is always positive"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Zero is represented as 0\/1"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Creating-BFractions","text":"Creating BFraction’s","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ From its numerator and denominator","let f = BFraction(17, 4)","","\/\/ From its decimal value","let f = BFraction(4.25)","","\/\/ From its string representation","let f = BFraction(\"4.25\")!","\/\/ or equivalently","let f = BFraction(\"425E-2\")!","","\/\/ From a continued fraction","let f = BFraction([3, 4, 12, 4])  \/\/ f = 649 \/ 200"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Defining a fraction by specifying its decimal value might lead to surprises,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"because not all decimal values can be represented exactly as a floating point number."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One might think that "},{"code":"BFraction(0.1)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" would equal 1\/10,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but in fact it equals 3602879701896397 \/ 36028797018963968 = 0.1000000000000000055511151231257827021181583404541015625"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On the other hand, "},{"code":"BFraction(\"0.1\")!","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" equals 1\/10."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Converting-BFractions","text":"Converting BFraction’s","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"BFraction values can be converted to String values, to decimal String values, to Double values and to Continued Fraction values."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let x = BFraction(1000, 7)","","\/\/ To String","let s1 = x.asString() \/\/ s1 = \"1000 \/ 7\"","","\/\/ To decimal String","let s1 = x.asDecimalString(precision: 8, exponential: false) \/\/ s1 = \"142.85714\"","let s2 = x.asDecimalString(precision: 8, exponential: true) \/\/ s2 = \"1.4285714E+2\"","","\/\/ To Double","let d = x.asDouble() \/\/ d = 142.8571428571429","","\/\/ To Continued Fraction","let f = x.asContinuedFraction() \/\/ f = [BInt(142), BInt(1), BInt(6)]"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Operations","text":"Operations","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The operations available to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/BFraction","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" are:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Arithmetic:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" addition, subtraction, multiplication, division, exponentiation, modulus"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Comparison:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" The six standard operations ==  !=  <  <=  >  >="}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rounding:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Rounding fractions to integers"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Miscellaneous:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Bernoulli Numbers, Harmonic Numbers"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Bernoulli-Numbers","text":"Bernoulli Numbers","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The static function"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let Bn = BFraction.bernoulli(n)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"computes the n’th (n >= 0) Bernoulli number, which is a rational number."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["print(BFraction.bernoulli(60))","print(BFraction.bernoulli(60).asDecimalString(precision: 20, exponential: true))"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"would print"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["-1215233140483755572040304994079820246041491 \/ 56786730","-2.1399949257225333665E+34"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The static function"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let x = BFraction.bernoulliSequence(n)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"computes the n even numbered Bernoulli numbers B(0), B(2) … B(2 * n - 2)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Harmonic-Numbers","text":"Harmonic Numbers","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The static function"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let Hn = BFraction.harmonic(n)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"computes the n’th harmonic number, that is, 1 + 1\/2 + … + 1\/n"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The static function"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let x = BFraction.harmonicSequence(n)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"returns an array containing the first n harmonic numbers."}]}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"BigInt"}],"title":"About BFraction","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/AboutBFraction","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://bigint.BigInt/documentation/BigInt/BInt":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"BInt","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/bigint.BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/BInt","title":"BInt","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The BInt structure"}],"url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/bint","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"BInt"}]},"doc://bigint.BigInt/documentation/BigInt/BFraction":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/bfraction","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"BFraction"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The BFraction structure"}],"title":"BFraction","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"BFraction","kind":"identifier"}],"